    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3549612581" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3549612581" />
    <a title="Plateresca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6672056-plateresca"><img alt="Plateresca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1630988873p2/6672056.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3549612581?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Plateresca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Plateresca" href="/user/show/6672056-plateresca">Plateresca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140435900" href="/book/show/80080.The_Golden_Ass">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6672056-plateresca?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3549612581" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3396425762739414669"><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/photos/1600166263p8/3940999.jpg' alt='The Golden Ass' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/>The difficulty with writing a review for this novel is, what do we compare it to? <br/>A lot of writers have borrowed from or been influenced by Apuleius, so it&apos;s good to be acquainted with his text. But the real meaning of it is often obscure, so the whole experience of reading it is quite peculiar.<br/><br/><b>What I liked:</b><br/>The witches here are powerful :) <br/>The ass is really, really in trouble. This has helped put my own preoccupations into perspective.<br/>There&apos;s a lot of humour.<br/>Everything is unpredictable and this</span>
  <span id="freeText3396425762739414669" style="display:none"><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/photos/1600166263p8/3940999.jpg" alt="The Golden Ass" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br>The difficulty with writing a review for this novel is, what do we compare it to? <br>A lot of writers have borrowed from or been influenced by Apuleius, so it's good to be acquainted with his text. But the real meaning of it is often obscure, so the whole experience of reading it is quite peculiar.<br><br><b>What I liked:</b><br>The witches here are powerful :) <br>The ass is really, really in trouble. This has helped put my own preoccupations into perspective.<br>There's a lot of humour.<br>Everything is unpredictable and this is rather a page-turner.<br><br><b>I'm not sure about it:</b><br>Scabrous anecdotes. Some of them are funny, and I certainly didn't hate them, but there's a disturbing anti-women-in-general slant in most of them.<br><br><b>I didn't enjoy:</b><br>Cruelty, including cruelty to animals. I understand this was typical of the epoch, and I hope with all my heart humanity is better in this respect now, but reading this book does not exactly open one's heart to other people.<br><br>***<br><br>The commentaries to this <b>Penguin Classics edition</b> are quite helpful.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3396425762739414669" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

