        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3916426631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15678805097627513441">I had to read this one for my Ancient Roman history class. There were definitely some amusing bits and scenes where I found myself surprisingly absorbed in the story, but overall I didn&apos;t find the book to be either entertaining or meaningful to warrant 3 stars. This book, as many will probably agree with me, didn&apos;t seem to have much of a point.<br/><br/>There were quite a few OTT moments, including at the end of the book a woman who slept with Lucius in the form of an ass. I still don&apos;t understand how his</span>
  <span id="freeText15678805097627513441" style="display:none">I had to read this one for my Ancient Roman history class. There were definitely some amusing bits and scenes where I found myself surprisingly absorbed in the story, but overall I didn't find the book to be either entertaining or meaningful to warrant 3 stars. This book, as many will probably agree with me, didn't seem to have much of a point.<br /><br />There were quite a few OTT moments, including at the end of the book a woman who slept with Lucius in the form of an ass. I still don't understand how his, ahem equipment, fit inside her. <br /><br />Also, the beginning of Psyche's story was SO boring here. I was familiar with the story, but I've definitely read more entertaining versions of that myth. <br /><br />Oh, and also don't tell my teacher that I didn't really read Books 9-11. What can I say--I got lazy? Thank god for Gradesaver, which provided the summaries for those chapters.</span>
